{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "See issue #205\r\n\r\nThis fix feels a bit hacky. The problem is that `ApplyPenaltyTime` calls `Restart` on the current checkpoint, which has teleporting effects on the 1st checkpoint of each task. This PR makes it so the restart is called before the skip, so that the new goal is overridden.\r\n\r\nIf anyone can think of a more elegant way of solving the issue, feel free to directly edit this PR.\r\n\r\n@dirk-thomas , do you think you could take a quick look?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>See issue <a href=\"#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/205/task-3-checkpoint-2-skip-spinning-and\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Task 3 / Checkpoint 2 Skip - Spinning and Flailing\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#205</s></a></p>\n<p>This fix feels a bit hacky. The problem is that <code>ApplyPenaltyTime</code> calls <code>Restart</code> on the current checkpoint, which has teleporting effects on the 1st checkpoint of each task. This PR makes it so the restart is called before the skip, so that the new goal is overridden.</p>\n<p>If anyone can think of a more elegant way of solving the issue, feel free to directly edit this PR.</p>\n<p>@dirk-thomas , do you think you could take a quick look?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Fix skipping before leaving the start box", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Fix skipping before leaving the start box</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "See issue #205\r\n\r\nThis fix feels a bit hacky. The problem is that `ApplyPenaltyTime` calls `Restart` on the current checkpoint, which has teleporting effects on the 1st checkpoint of each task. This PR makes it so the restart is called before the skip, so that the new goal is overridden.\r\n\r\nIf anyone can think of a more elegant way of solving the issue, feel free to directly edit this PR.\r\n\r\n@dirk-thomas , do you think you could take a quick look?", "links": {"decline": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/srcsi